</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-74"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-74">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#Reference-Graney-2015">Graney (2015, pp. 71)</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-75">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#Reference-Graney-2015">Graney (2015, pp. 66-76, 164-175, 187-195)</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-wcumf-76"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-wcumf_76-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Finocchiaro, Maurice. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070930013053/http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html#conreport">"West Chester University\xe2\x80\x94History of Astronomy; Lecture notes: Texts from The Galileo Affair: A Documentary History"</a>. West Chester University. ESS 362 / 562. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html#conreport">the original</a> on 30 September 2007<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">18 February</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.aufirst=Maurice&amp;rft.aulast=Finocchiaro&amp;rft.btitle=West+Chester+University%E2%80%94History+of+Astronomy%3B+Lecture+notes%3A+Texts+from+The+Galileo+Affair%3A+A+Documentary+History&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=West+Chester+University&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fastro.wcupa.edu%2Fmgagne%2Fess362%2Fresources%2Ffinocchiaro.html%23conreport&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://esmateria.com/2014/02/28/una-errata-reproducida-durante-siglos-cambia-la-censura-de-la-iglesia-a-galileo/">"Una errata reproducida durante siglos cambia la censura de la Iglesia a Galileo"</a>. <i>Materia</i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.atitle=Una+errata+reproducida+durante+siglos+cambia+la+censura+de+la+Iglesia+a+Galileo&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Materia&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fesmateria.com%2F2014%2F02%2F28%2Funa-errata-reproducida-durante-siglos-cambia-la-censura-de-la-iglesia-a-galileo%2F&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-h218-78"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-h218_78-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-h218_78-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Heilbron (2010), p. 218</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-79"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Sharratt <a href="#Reference-Sharratt-1994">(1994</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=rB0rHzrpJOMC&amp;pg=PA126#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false">pp. 126\xe2\x80\x9331)</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Pope_Urban_VIII-80"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Pope_Urban_VIII_80-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://galileo.rice.edu/gal/urban.html">"Pope Urban VIII Biography"</a>. <i>Galileo Project</i>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.atitle=Pope+Urban+VIII+Biography&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Galileo+Project&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgalileo.rice.edu%2Fgal%2Furban.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-81"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-81">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#Reference-Finocchiaro-1997">Finocchiaro (1997)</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Li4eh7JIMtIC&amp;pg=PA82">p. 82</a>; <a href="#Reference-Moss.26Wallace-2003">Moss &amp; Wallace (2003)</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Lw50esHmgacC&amp;pg=PA11">p. 11</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-82">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See Langford <a href="#Reference-Langford-1998">(1966, pp. 133\xe2\x80\x9334)</a>, and Seeger <a href="#Reference-Seeger-1966">(1966, p. 30)</a>, for example. Drake <a href="#Reference-Drake-1978">(1978, p. 355)</a> asserts that Simplicio\'s character is modelled on the Aristotelian philosophers Lodovico delle Colombe and <a href="/wiki/Cesare_Cremonini_(philosopher)" title="Cesare Cremonini (philosopher)">Cesare Cremonini</a>, rather than Urban. He also considers that the demand for Galileo to include the Pope\'s argument in the <i>Dialogue</i> left him with no option but to put it in the mouth of Simplicio <a href="#Reference-Drake-1953">(Drake, 1953, p. 491)</a>. Even <a href="/wiki/Arthur_Koestler" title="Arthur Koestler">Arthur Koestler</a>, who is generally quite harsh on Galileo in <i><a href="/wiki/The_Sleepwalkers" title="The Sleepwalkers">The Sleepwalkers</a></i> <a href="#Reference-Koestler-1990">(1959)</a>, after noting that Urban suspected Galileo of having intended Simplicio to be a caricature of him, says "this of course is untrue" <a href="#Reference-Koestler-1990">(1959, p. 483)</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-83"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-83">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Lindberg, David. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.asa3.org/ASA/PSCF/1987/PSCF9-87Lindberg.html">"Beyond War and Peace: A Reappraisal of the Encounter between Christianity and Science"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rft.aulast=Lindberg&amp;rft.btitle=Beyond+War+and+Peace%3A+A+Reappraisal+of+the+Encounter+between+Christianity+and+Science&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.asa3.org%2FASA%2FPSCF%2F1987%2FPSCF9-87Lindberg.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-84"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-84">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Sharratt (<a href="#Reference-Sharratt-1994">1994</a>, pp. 171\xe2\x80\x9375); Heilbron (<a href="#CITEREFHeilbron2010">2010</a>, pp. 308\xe2\x80\x9317); Gingerich (<a href="#Reference-Gingerich-1992">1992</a>, pp. 117\xe2\x80\x9318).</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-85"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-85">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#Reference-Fantoli-2005">Fantoli (2005, p. 139)</a>, <a href="#Reference-Finocchiaro-1989">Finocchiaro (1989, pp. 288\xe2\x80\x9393)</a>. Finocchiaro\'s translation of the Inquisition\'s judgement against Galileo is <cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070930013053/http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html">"available on-line"</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html">the original</a> on 30 September 2007<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2007-09-30</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.btitle=available+on-line&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fastro.wcupa.edu%2Fmgagne%2Fess362%2Fresources%2Ffinocchiaro.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. "Vehemently suspect of heresy" was a technical term of <a href="/wiki/Canon_law" title="Canon law">canon law</a> and did not necessarily imply that the Inquisition considered the opinions giving rise to the verdict to be heretical. The same verdict would have been possible even if the opinions had been subject to only the less serious censure of "erroneous in faith" <a href="#Reference-Fantoli-2005">(Fantoli, 2005, p. 140</a>; <a href="#Reference-Heilbron-2005">Heilbron, 2005, pp. 282\xe2\x80\x9384)</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-86"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-86">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#Reference-Finocchiaro-1989">Finocchiaro (1989</a>, pp. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=wKCZFJuMCaQC&amp;pg=PA38#v=onepage&amp;f=false">38</a>, 291, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=wKCZFJuMCaQC&amp;pg=PA306#v=onepage&amp;f=false">306)</a>. Finocchiaro\'s translation of the Inquisition\'s judgement against Galileo is <cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070930013053/http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html">"available on-line"</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://astro.wcupa.edu/mgagne/ess362/resources/finocchiaro.html">the original</a> on 30 September 2007<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2007-09-30</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGalileo+Galilei&amp;rft.btitle=available+on-line&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fastro.wcupa.edu%2Fmgagne%2Fess362%2Fresources%2Ffinocchiaro.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3